headline: Why I Can't Stop Buying These 2 Top High-Yield Dividend Stocks
summary: PepsiCo has increased its dividend for 53 straight years.  Vici Properties has grown its payout at an above-average rate since its formation.  My strategy is to continually invest in income-generating assets to steadily grow my passive income to the point where it can cover my basic living expenses.

headline: This Investing Pro Delivers a 5.5% Yield With Low Volatility. Here Are His Secrets.
summary: Ed Perks, manager of the 73-year-old Franklin Income Fund, is investing equally in stocks and bonds, often from the same companies. He shares some picks.
